Preheat oven to 350 degrees F. Spray large nonstick ovenproof skillet with cooking spray. Heat on medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook 3 min. on each side or until lightly browned on both sides. Remove from heat. Place onion on top of chicken; place apples around sides of chicken. Mix syrup and dressing; pour over chicken. Bake 20 to 25 min. or until chicken is cooked through. Spoon syrup mixture in skillet over chicken just before serving.